### 3. Likert Scale Columns (1–5)

All columns below use a standard 5-point Likert scale:

| Code | Label |
|------|-------|
| 1 | Strongly Disagree |
| 2 | Disagree |
| 3 | Neutral |
| 4 | Agree |
| 5 | Strongly Agree |

| Column | Survey Question (abbreviated) |
|--------|-------------------------------|
| `branded_quality` | Branded products offer better quality than unbranded products |
| `unbranded_is_vfm` | Unbranded products are value for money |
| `brand__is_confidence` | I feel more confident using branded products in social situations |
| `mumbai_brand_influence` | People in Mumbai are influenced by brand image while shopping |
| `social_media_influence` | Social media and advertisements influence my choice of branded products |
| `local_market_influence` | Local markets in Mumbai influence my decision to buy unbranded products |
| `mall_influence` | Shopping malls and branded stores influence my preference for branded products |
| `price_consciousness` | Rising cost of living in Mumbai makes me more price-conscious |

> **Note:** `brand__is_confidence` has a double underscore — this matches the raw column name from the survey export and is preserved as-is in the PostgreSQL schema.

